elements.title: Ron Miles (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Ron Miles (pictured), who would have turned 59 today, played in the same high school jazz band as Don Cheadle?

elements.title: attack on the Delhi chief minister's residence (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that during the attack on the Delhi chief minister's residence, protesters painted the gate red and tried to scale it while police officers watched?

elements.title: Francis Orray Ticknor (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Francis Orray Ticknor was a country doctor whose fame as a poet relies on "Little Giffen", a poem about one of his patients who died in the American Civil War?

elements.title: Du, o schönes Weltgebäude (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the 1653 hymn "Du, o schönes Weltgebäude", about renouncing the world, contains the stanza "Komm, O Tod, des Schlafes Bruder", which Bach used to conclude his cross-staff cantata?

elements.title: Satyagraha Hoerip (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Satyagraha Hoerip wrote a short story set during the Indonesian mass killings of 1965–66 from the perspective of the killers-to-be?

elements.title: NBA Comeback Player of the Year Award (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the NBA Comeback Player of the Year Award was canceled, reportedly because of drugs?

elements.title: call to prayer (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that a call to prayer is a common feature to Christianity, Islam and Judaism?

elements.title: Recess Therapy (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that topics on Recess Therapy have included the economy, climate change, and peeing your pants?
